dig, dig ...the DAV spec says "URI". 
This was the way I was leaning, too. 
The main question that made me wonder was, suppose someone wants to define a type of namespace that's defined by something other than a URI? 
(In such a case, it might be best to be able to swap out the href element for something else.) However, I think the answer is that they should just define a new URI scheme. 
